Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and dialogue systems. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes end-to-end neural network models for simulating users in task-oriented dialogue systems. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed models use recurrent neural networks and a latent variable model. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the importance of user simulation for evaluating and training dialogue systems. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with spoken dialogue systems.
